 <p><P><u><font face="Roman" size="+1" color="Navy"><b>Lurik Crim'Tal</b></font></u><BR>
<b><font face="Roman" size="-1" color="Black">Proud leader of the Veiled Alliance<BR>
Apprentice of Nimbel Fyngers and Zappalan Greymist<BR>
Server Rodcet Nife</font><BR><BR><font color="green">"DEFINATELY get your mask, it's still worth having even if we both are superior Dark Elves already." - Durden Darkpoint</b></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/udarthender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarthEnder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/01 2:40:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2090.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Talk Item List - Absor</span><hr size=1> I'm gonna go through these one by one...<br>
<br>
Ecade:  It's already been talked to death.  No need to discuss it any more here.<br>
<br>
Damage Shields and missiles:  Hope they fix it.<br>
<br>
Locked Chests:  That would be damn cool.  Never even thought of that.<br>
<br>
Report Backstab messages to a group:  Eh.  It's okay.  I still wanted a Thunder Kick style discipline to do this though, not every backstab.<br>
<br>
Sneak and Hide functionality:  Two items here.  The ungreying thing is good.  I got killed 3 times buy the lesser mummy in Nektulos trying to loot my body before I figured out what was up.<br>
As for the sneaking and merchant thing...I HOPE THEY DO FIX THIS!  It is a BUG.  It's ALWAYS been a bug.  There is no way in hell that sneaking was designed to allow you to trade and hail every npc in the game as if you had indifferent faction.  The 'secret handshake' was a nice little excuse developed by the rogue community, but it's @#%$.  It's a SIDE EFFECT to the way sneak works, not the intention.  Granted, if they correct this, some rogue quests will probably have to be fixed slightly, but OH WELL.  Sneak is not 'working as intended'.  And I'll not pretent that it is simply because I like what the bug does for me.<br>
<br>
Haste for missile weapons:  Good idea.  I didn't even know it didn't do that already.  Should work for bows too.<br>
<br>
Illusion mask:  Not being able to turn them off is stupid.<br>
<br>
Hide/sneak overwriting invisibility:  Yes, clicking hide should immidiatly cancel out and invis spell you have running on you.<br>
<br>
Increased Safefall:  Yep.  Sure would be nice.<br>
<br>
Sneaking in water:  I think they are right that it should be consistent, but in the way that you should be able to activate sneak while in the water.<br>
<br>
Stackable poisons:  Arguably the MOST important thing.  This needs to be fixed.<br>
<br>
Poisoning in Full screen mode:  It doesn't?  I though that was only if you had the item in a bag.  Oh well.  If that's true they better fix it.<br>
<br>
Sneak skill increases:  Um, okay.  Not really important.  But I guess if they do this with sneak, they should do it with hide too.<br>
<br>
Speed increase whil hide and sneaking:  Well, my personal take is that this should be linked to your sneaking skill, not your level.  As for the increasing it to faster than it is now...at max now, you sneak as fast as you run.  You want us to move FASTER while sneaking than running?  Der.<br>
<br>
Tracking:  Ugh.  This is so stupid.  Why do people keep asking for it?<br>
<br>
Sense Traps:  HAven't really used them on Velious traps yet so I can't comment.<br>
<br>
Stun with backstab:  One of my favorite ideas.  I can see how THIS would be difficult to code(much more so than some of the other things they say they can't code).<br>
<br>
Poison on thrown weapons:  Nice if it happens.  But even I can see pvp balance issues.  But then PvP rogues say that melee are already way underpowered in PvP, so maybe this is a good idea.<br>
<br>
Soulbound lockpicks:  Don't see how this is hard, unless finding a place to but them in the game is the hard part.<br>
<br>
Apply poison animation:  Didn't they already say this was PROBABLY gonna happen?  Why is it n/a?<br>
<br>
Throwing weapons:  Yep.  I say add fletched darts.  Fix two skills at once.<br>
<br>
Set traps:  Could be fun, but I won't hold my breath waiting.  The traps would have to be tinkered as well.<br>
<br>
Hide/sneak across zone borders:  Not to mention when going LD or camping.  This is also arguably the most important thing that needs fixing.  Too bad it's all the way at the bottom.<br>
<br>
Anyway.  That's just how I feel. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dboulais_1999/Thief03.jpg">
